cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the use of logic programming and aggregates, which are commonly used in AI applications.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper extends concepts from normal logic programming to programs with monotone and convex constraints, making it relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses properties of programs and program completion, which are relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper mentions the use of off-the-shelf solvers of pseudo-boolean constraints, which are commonly used in optimization algorithms.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper discusses the use of monotone and convex constraints, which are topics in discrete mathematics.
